[9] PAHO epidemiological update
Date: Thu 18 Apr 2019
Source: Pan American Health Organization (PAHO) Epidemiological Alerts and Updates [abridged, edited]
https://www.paho.org/hq/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1239:epidemiological-alerts-updates&Itemid=2291&lang=en


Between epidemiological week (EW) 1 and EW 9 of 2019, 10 countries in the Region of the Americas have reported confirmed cases occurring between December 2018 and February 2019: Argentina, the Bahamas, Brazil, Canada, Chile, Colombia, Costa Rica, Mexico, the United States of America, and the Bolivarian Republic of Venezuela. No fatal cases have been reported in 2019.

